el="Topic" /><category relevance="100" term="Hobbies and Pastimes" label="Topic" /><category relevance="95" term="Professional Football" label="Topic" /><category relevance="95" term="Sports" label="Topic" /><category relevance="100" term="Video Games" label="Topic" /><generator>(c) Postmedia Network Inc.</generator><link href="http://www.dose.ca/6064414.ATOM" rel="alternate" type="application/atom+xml" title="Review: NFL Blitz" /><link href="http://www.dose.ca/6064414.ATOM" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" title="Review: NFL Blitz" /><entry Status="FREE"><id>tag:www.dose.ca:content=6064414</id><title type="html">Review: NFL Blitz</title><summary type="html"></summary><published>2012-01-27T00:00:00Z</published><updated>2012-01-28T01:15:45Z</updated><author><name>Paul Chapman</name></author><link href="Review+Blitz/6064414/story.html" Abstract="NFL Blitz is a fun romp for football fans." Credit="Paul Chapman" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="[ more ]" /><link rel="canonical" href="http://www.theprovince.com/entertainment/Review+Blitz/6064414/story.html" /><link href="6063865.bin" Abstract="NFL Blitz is a fun romp if you're not about realism." Credit="submitted" rel="enclosure" type="image/jpeg" title="NFLBlitz" /><link href="http://www.ea.com/nfl-blitz" Abstract="NFL Blitz web site" Credit="" rel="related" type="text/html" title="NFL Blitz web site" /><category term="Gaming" label="ConTopic" /><category term="The Province" label="Distributor" /><category term="STRY" label="ContentTypeCode" /><category term="VAPR" label="Catalog" /><category term="Y" label="Comments" /><category term="UTF8" label="Format" /><category relevance="75" term="Facebook Inc." label="Company" /><category relevance="28" term="FOX Broadcasting Company" label="Company" /><category relevance="38" term="FOX News Network LLC" label="Company" /><category relevance="38" term="The Wall Street Journal" label="Company" /><category relevance="38" term="TMZ.com Inc." label="Company" /><category relevance="75" term="Twitter Inc." label="Company" /><category relevance="14" term="World Wrestling Entertainment Inc." label="Company" /><category relevance="100" term="317~Sony PlayStation3~National Football League~Microsoft Xbox 360~Facebook Inc." label="InformQString" /><category relevance="29" term="Family Guy" label="Misc" /><category relevance="95" term="National Football League" label="Organization" /><category relevance="29" term="Ultimate Fighting Championship" label="Organization" /><category relevance="30" term="Fruit Ninja" label="Product" /><category relevance="88" term="Microsoft Xbox 360" label="Product" /><category relevance="29" term="Microsoft Xbox Live" label="Product" /><category relevance="100" term="Sony PlayStation3" label="Product" /><category relevance="100" term="Culture and Lifestyle" label="Topic" /><category relevance="100" term="Entertainment" label="Topic" /><category relevance="95" term="Football" label="Topic" /><category relevance="100" term="Games" label="Topic" /><category relevance="100" term="Hobbies and Pastimes" label="Topic" /><category relevance="95" term="Professional Football" label="Topic" /><category relevance="95" term="Sports" label="Topic" /><category relevance="100" term="Video Games" label="Topic" /><content type="xhtml"><div id="1">&lt;P&gt;Last week I lamented the dearth of any new games in the last two months.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;It hasn’t got much better but at least, with a spare week in between the NFL Conference Championships and the Super Bowl there is NFL Blitz for the PlayStation 3 and the Xbox 360.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;This is the over-the-top frenetic football game with real NFL players. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Well, real in name at least. This is cartoonish football where players catch fire, turn into indestructible, untackleable players and big hits can take out a whole team like a bowling ball.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;It’s also a bit like playing the cheapest game known to man, you can actually use strategy (say, you beat an all-out blitz and score a bit play for a touchdown), and get a 21-point lead, but then everything is going to go against you and the score will even out.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;That can be frustrating, there are no blowouts, only close games down to the last play. If you accept that the game is a complete romp and full of randomness and less about skill, it is a blast for every football fan.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Even those who sometimes get bored with the clinical 40-minute Madden NFL games, this will give you a blast of football with little thought to realism and get you in and out of the game in a hurry.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;It’s the hybrid of a lot of the Madden features though that makes Blitz a lot more fun.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;They have the Ultimate Team Mode where you can earn points while you play, then spend your points on packs of cards that let you “win” big NFL stars.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;If you’re playing online against other players, and are confident in your ability, you can bet your cards in Risk vs. Reward. If you win, you get to steal one of his players but if you lose, your hard earned stars could be pilfered too.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Online is pretty much the best way to play as there isn’t the cheapness that you find when the AI really tries to even things out.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;There is an Elite League format to play with that keeps regional leaderboards, but to be honest the most fun is playing against friends. It’s a mixture of WWE and the NFL and the outlandish characters, moves and effects and ultimately, a lot of fun.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Rating: E for Everyone&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;What’s right: Fast-paced, quick games, pure arcade fun;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;What’s wrong: Very cheap gameplay.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Numb Thumb: Graphics B; Gameplay C+; Value C+. Overall a C+ on the Numb Thumb&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;News and notes&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Going back to the launch of the Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3, one of the biggest selling points over time for me with the PS3 was the browser. Though the 360 was attached to the web only really through Xbox Live, the PS3 let you roam freely on the web.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;While the 360 never has allowed the browser, the new interface allows you to use all sorts of apps. In the past they’ve added the social media capabilities, with Facebook and Twitter, but also added UFC and TMZ. They have recently announced more applications with Disney XC and Real Sports (Maple Leaf Sports and Entertainment). Also on the way are FOX programming, including Family Guy along with Wall Street Journal, Fox News and more. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Star Wars&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Videogames and Star Wars always draw big numbers. So it was a pretty smart marketing move for Brisk soft drinks to team up and create a lightsaber app. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Sort of like Fruit Ninja with the legendary laser sword from the Star Wars, you slice your way through levels and try to climb up the global leaderboard.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The app is a pretty cool little time waster, check it out at. http://itunes.apple.com/ca/app/brisksaber-canada/id492709176? mt=8&amp;amp;ls=1. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;It’s also available for download via Facebook.com/BriskCanada.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Twitter: @paulc14&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</div></content><rights type="text">Copyright (c) The Province</rights><source><title type="html">Review: NFL Blitz</title><subtitle type="html">NFL Blitz is a fun romp for football fans.</subtitle><id>tag:www.dose.ca:content=6064414</id><rights type="html">Copyright (c) The Province</rights><updated>2012-01-28T01:15:45Z</updated><category term="Gaming" label="ConTopic" /><category term="The Province" label="Distributor" /><category term="STRY" label="ContentTypeCode" /><category term="VAPR" label="Catalog" /><category term="Y" label="Comments" /><category term="UTF8" label="Format" /><category relevance="75" ter